              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/55240303-ren-hiatus?shelf=tear-jerker">tear-jerker</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3434097993" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7931345959857264231">There&apos;s a certain ✨charm✨ about this book that I have yet to find in other HR romances. I went into this book blind and had no idea it was going to be this FUNNY!! It&apos;s been a while since I&apos;ve laughed the whole way through a book and I can definitely see why it&apos;s such a popular favorite! Jaimie&apos;s quirkiness and Alec&apos;s gruffness created such a passionate and fun romance. I liked the way they tried to navigate their marriage even though they kept stepping on each other&apos;s toes! Jaimie and Alec did </span>
  <span id="freeText7931345959857264231" style="display:none">There's a certain ✨charm✨ about this book that I have yet to find in other HR romances. I went into this book blind and had no idea it was going to be this FUNNY!! It's been a while since I've laughed the whole way through a book and I can definitely see why it's such a popular favorite! Jaimie's quirkiness and Alec's gruffness created such a passionate and fun romance. I liked the way they tried to navigate their marriage even though they kept stepping on each other's toes! Jaimie and Alec did not fail to amuse me at every turn. <i>The Bride</i> is definitely a must-read for HR fans.<br /><br /><b>Rating:</b> 4/5</span>
